understand the developmentel model:-Android is a mobile operating system based on a modified version of the Linux kernel and other open-source software, designed primarily for touchscreen mobile devices such as smartphones and tablets.
license:- The majority of the Android platform and documentation is licensed under the Apache 2.0 license.
However most devices run on the proprietary Android version developed by Google, which ship with additional proprietary closed-source software pre-installed

